column1: VsysRadio: CO radio helocentric vsys (km/s); see VsysFlag for how this was derived
VsysRel: CO vsys after relativistic correction (km/s)
PA: position angle in degrees; ranges from 0-365 degrees; see PAFlag for how this was derived
Inc: inclination in degrees; see IncFlag for how this was derived
RA: RA of central pixel from CRVAL
Dec: Dec of central pixel from CRVAL
l: galactic longitude of central pixel calculated from RA and Dec
b: galactic latitude of central pixel calculated from RA and Dec
xoff: x-offset of center from central pixel; this is 0 unless the center position is very far off
Rmax: maximum radius in arcsec from the center for which ringfit places a ring; this already subtracts NumBadEndRings; 0 indicates no/not enough data
VRotMax: maximum rotational velocity at Rmax in km/s in relativistic frame; 0 indicates no/not enough data
yoff: y-offset of center from central pixel; this is 0 unless the center position is very far off
NumBadEndRings: the number of outer rings to discard due to poor fits from ringfit
PAFlag: this describes where the PA listed is from; 0=ringfit results; 1=outer optical isophotes; 2=LEDA
IncFlag: this describes where the inclination listed is from; 0=ringfit results; 1=outer optical isophotes; 2=LEDA
VsysFlag: this describes where the CO radio vsys listed is from; 0=ringfit results; 2=LEDA
